TORCS Installation instructions on Linux:

Requisites:
-----------
            OpenGl or a recent Mesa (http://mesa3d.sourceforge.net/)
            GLUT 3.7 or later (http://reality.sgi.com/mjk/glut3/glut3.html)
            Or FreeGlut (not tested) (http://freeglut.sourceforge.net/)
            PLIB 1.4.2 (http://plib.sourceforge.net/) patched with plib-smoothing.dif
            libpng (http://www.libpng.org/pub/png/libpng.html)
	    zlib (for libpng)
            a driver if you have a 3D card (recommended) (http://www.linux3D.org)
            a joystick driver. (mandatory to drive yourself, don't forget to calibrate !!!)
	                       (http://atrey.karlin.mff.cuni.cz/~vojtech/joystick)

Installation:
-------------

1 - decompress the sources tar ball: 

      $ tar xzvf torcs-xxx-src*.tgz

2 - build the executables 

      $ cd torcs-xxx
      $ ./configure [--prefix=PREFIX (default /usr/local)]
      $ make
      $ make install         # installs in PREFIX/games/torcs PREFIX/bin and PREFIX/lib

This should generate the binaries, with no more than few warnings.

4 - decompress the mandatory data:

      $ cd PREFIX/games/torcs
      $ tar xzvf torcs-xxx-data.tgz

5 - decompress the optionnal data:

      $ tar xzvf torcs-xxx-data-*.tgz

6- run TORCS 

 if PREFIX/bin is not in your $PATH

      $ cd PREFIX/bin
      $ ./torcs                    

 else
      $ torcs

4- Enjoy

